data.enText: to kill sb/sth in a war or a fight

data.chText: 两名乘客遭劫机者杀害。
data.enText: Two passengers were slain by the hijackers.
to have a strong effect on sb

data.chText: 那些老影片依旧让我着迷！
data.enText: Those old movies still slay me!

data.chText: 那宗和毒品有关的五人被杀的案子
data.enText: the drug-related slayings of five people

ex.chText: 他的妻子在一次车祸中丧生。
ex.enText: His wife was killed in a car accident.

ex.chText: 总统在上班路上被杀了。
ex.enText: The president was killed on his way to the office.

synonyms.bx: 普通用词，泛指以任何方式使人、动物或植物死亡。

ex.chText: 警方已破获一起暗杀总统的阴谋。
ex.enText: The police have uncovered a plot to assassinate the president.

ex.chText: 恐怖分子在密谋暗杀这位总统候选人。
ex.enText: Terrorists are plotting to assassinate the presidential candidate.

synonyms.bx: 主要指出于政治原因采用非法手段杀害重要人物或知名人士。

ex.chText: 昨天夜里管家被谋杀了。
ex.enText: The housekeeper was murdered last night.

ex.chText: 他被判谋杀一名女警察的罪名成立。
ex.enText: He was convicted of murdering a policewoman.
Three passengers were slain by the hijackers.

ex.chText: 昨天有数名游客惨遭杀害。
ex.enText: Several visitors were brutally slain yesterday.

synonyms.bx: 指残酷地杀害某人，尤用于新闻报道中。

example: The mafia boss ordered his enemies murdered

value.def: If someone slays an animal, they kill it in a violent way.

example.ex: ...the hill where St George slew the dragon.
The festival commemorates the slaying of the demon buffalo.
example.tran: 那个节日是为了纪念杀死魔牛。

value.def: If someone has been slain, they have been murdered.

example.tran: 两名澳大利亚游客被杀。
